# General conventions

## File organisation

```
src/
  config.py          # Pydantic Settings — all env vars
  models/            # ORM + Pydantic models (one file per entity)
  routes/            # FastAPI route handlers (one file per resource)
  dependencies/      # Reusable FastAPI Depends functions
  domain/            # Pure business logic (no I/O)
  services/          # Stateful service classes (DB + external calls)
  workers/           # Background consumers and publishers
  jobs/              # CLI jobs (export, GDPR redaction)
  errors/            # Error envelope + exception handlers
  observability/     # Structured logging + Prometheus metrics
tests/
  unit/              # No I/O; @pytest.mark.unit
  integration/       # Real Postgres; @pytest.mark.integration
  contracts/         # Stub validators; @pytest.mark.contract
  e2e/               # Full stack; @pytest.mark.e2e
  security/          # Auth + PAN-leak checks; @pytest.mark.security
```

## Naming

| Thing | Convention |
|---|---|
| Modules | `snake_case` |
| Pydantic models | `PascalCase` (e.g. `CardCreate`, `TransactionRead`) |
| ORM models | `PascalCase` + `ORM` suffix (e.g. `CardORM`) |
| Route functions | `snake_case`, verb-first (e.g. `issue_card`) |
| Dependency functions | `require_` prefix (e.g. `require_auth`) |
| Enum values | `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` |
| Error codes | `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` (e.g. `CARDHOLDER_NOT_VERIFIED`) |

## Imports

- Absolute imports only; no relative `..` chains beyond one level.
- Group: stdlib → third-party → internal, separated by blank lines.

## Comments

- Avoid prose comments that restate what the code does.
- A comment is warranted only for non-obvious regulatory constraints, timing invariants, or known workarounds.
- Regulatory constraints: cite the standard (e.g. `# PCI DSS v4.0 Req 3.3 — SAD must not be stored`).

